snippet: Iran has started cutting back on some nuclear technology, but diplomats cautioned that it was keeping thousands of machines on standby that could be used for military purposes.
abstract: International Atomic Energy Agency reports Iran has sidelined some centrifuges in compliance with nuclear pact but some diplomats caution they could still be restarted quickly.
lead_paragraph: Iran has started cutting back on some nuclear technology, but diplomats cautioned that it was keeping thousands of machines on standby that could be used for military purposes.
